# Weather Vibes Spec Rule

- Treat `specs/weatherVibes.md` as the source of truth for weather vibe behavior.
- Read `specs/weatherVibes.md` before adding or changing recipe entries.
- Use `months: Month[]` on recipes (same format as seasonal produce; use `ALL_MONTHS` for year-round).
- Only use canonical vibe values: `cozy`, `hearty`, `fresh`, `lightWarm`, `any`.
- Preserve the `any` fallback invariants defined in `specs/weatherVibes.md`.
- Keep weather-to-vibe mapping and tests aligned with the spec.
